<div id="post-843" class="cf post-843 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

	<h2>
		<span class="post-format"></span>
		<a href="http://werblog.com/2003/08/the-day-email-died/" title="The Day Email Died?" rel="bookmark">The Day Email Died?</a>
		
	</h2>

	
	
	<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
	
		<div class="post-date">		
			<p class="post-month">Aug</p>
			<p class="post-day">20</p>
			<p class="post-year">2003</p>				
		</div>

		Between 10:45pm last night and 6am this morning, I received 1,470 pieces of spam (a run rate of nearly 5,000 per day). Most of them were from the SoBig worm, which seems to be the worst yet. And as far as I can tell, it&#8217;s still getting worse. I wonder if this is the last straw that will convince people to move in droves to challenge/response or whitelist mechanisms, as ...
		
	</div>

